      <entry xml:id="Slips_BroadfordMFarmerslips-idp161832456">
        <form>
          <orth>sgaimeic</orth>
        </form>
        <def>Quotation: sgaimeic (hd) – pronounced as if with -hd. Notes: stressed syllable has /ɛ/ sound. Has general meaning of ‘a mess’. Could be used of foods mixed together which aren’t usually
          mixed. Phrase ‘Rinn e s. dheth’ could be used of someone who’s messed some job up. [NOTES: on this slip ‘Broadford’ was crossed out and replaced with ‘Breakish’.]</def>
